The release Actions log shows:
  plymouth-set-default-theme azurelinux --rebuild-initrd

The helper delegates to bare `dracut -f`, which selects the build
container's uname rather than the target Azure kernel. The next-build
workflow explicitly rebuilds each /usr/lib/modules kernel instead.

Disposable qcow2 overlay validation:
  target kernel: 6.18.31-1.5.azl4.x86_64
  commands:
    plymouth-set-default-theme azurelinux
    dracut --force --kver 6.18.31-1.5.azl4.x86_64
  result: the rebuilt target initramfs contains details.so, script.so,
  azurelinux.plymouth, azurelinux.script, azurelinuxlogo.png, dot.png,
  and dot-glow.png.
  qemu-img check: no errors.

Second disk-path requirement:
  The released BLS entry has only `console=ttyS0`; it does not request
  `rhgb quiet`. Rebuilding the initramfs alone therefore does not guarantee
  that Plymouth is started. The next build writes `rhgb quiet` into existing
  BLS entries and the kernel-install hook for future entries.
